To think of a life without you is unimaginable. To think of our love without being able to seal it with not only God’s approval but the final copy of our marriage certificate would be devastating. 

1966 it was against the law for interracial couples to Marry. By 1967 the Supreme Court Case, Loving vs. Virginia made it legal to Marry as an interracial couple. My kids can grow to see the love Aaron and I have for one another in matrimony. 

There are so many things wrong in the world that need to be made right but loving who you love should never be a crime or against the law. Our voices matter, our hearts matter, our lives matter. Today is a reminder that WE MATTER 🤎

Thank You ✊🏾✊🏻✊🏿✊🏼✊🏽

God knew exactly what he was doing blessing me with such an amazing husband and a wonderful and present father my kids. 

Our daughters first love after God is their father and that is the greatest gift I could ever ask for. 

Watching the bond between our girls and their dad brings me to tears everytime! So much that it has taken me so much time to come up with the words I wanted to say from my heart, I cried every time I began to write this post just thinking of how blessed we truly are. 

The journey we have been on has been rough, the pregnancies that didn’t make it, our daughter that we lost, to now holding two blessings in your arms forever. I’m so thankful that God chose you for me and to be the father of our beautiful daughters. I’d live the same story over and over if it meant that I get to live it with you. 

Happy Father’s Day ! I love you 🥹

Happy Father’s Day to all of the amazing dads out there ! We love you and appreciate you!

Sunday night we randomly decided to go to the beach and watch the sunset. 

We went to our nearest @meijerstores and picked up some hot dogs and all the items for s’mores.

I said I was going to start posting weekend dumps and I totally forgot to post these on Sunday.

Friday was the first morning of Elf On The Shelf. The kids woke up and were so excited and happy to see our Elf Pretty. 

Saturday the girls and I were invited to bake some Christmas cookies with friends. We had so much fun and are probably still high off of joy and sugar. 

Saturday night we enjoyed watching some Michigan football and let the girls stay up late to cheer Michigan on! 

Sunday we spent all day outside playing in the snow. Before we moved here I never played in the snow for more than 5 seconds! But Michigan snow is just a little bit different than Indiana snow and I LOVE IT! 

Sunday night I poured my love into a fancy dinner for my little family. We set the table and made it fancy for the girls with a little Sparkling Cider. I always find ways to show love to my family outside of hugs, kisses, and time. Cooking for my family and making it special is my way of showing them I love them. 

Hoping everyone had a great weekend and are off to an amazing start to the week.

Our first Christmas together was just us 2 as college students, not having a clue what life had in store. 

1 Snapchat later and here we are with 2 beautiful baby girls and happily married. Living in a home we prayed so hard for, and raising the children we prayed for. 

God truly blessed us with our little family. Creating NEW traditions outside of our own family traditions while also keeping the original ones has been so refreshing and full of joy.
